The '''Defense Blood Standard System''' (DBSS) is a [[Food and Drug Administration|FDA]]-regulated, Class II Medical Device designed to handle blood collection, processing and tracking procedures, and automation of standards and safeguards for the [[Military Health System]] (MHS) blood supply.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.dodig.mil/audit/reports/fy02/02010sum.htm | title=Armed Services Blood Program Defense Blood Standard System | work=Department of Defense | date=22 October 2001 | accessdate=9 August 2015}}</ref> DBSS is also identified by the FDA as a Blood Establishment Software item.

The DBSS supports the Armed Services Blood Program Office, which manages the blood program for the [[United States Department of Defense|Department of Defense]], and services more than 8.7 million MHS beneficiaries.

